overview: "The user initiated a request to resolve a wide array of issues within
  a pull request, encompassing critical security flaws, various functional bugs,
  and persistent Vercel deployment failures. The process involved a systematic
  approach to code remediation: fixing lint errors, implementing a robust
  HMAC-based session management system compatible with Vercel's Edge Runtime,
  validating API parameters, enhancing PDF generation accuracy, and improving
  form field handling. A significant challenge arose when Vercel deployments
  continued to fail, leading to the discovery and resolution of a critical
  Next.js security vulnerability (CVE-2025-66478) by updating to version 16.1.1.
  This update, in turn, necessitated further adjustments to the Prisma
  configuration due to breaking changes in Prisma 7 and a complete overhaul of
  the ESLint setup as the  command was deprecated. While all
  code-related issues were successfully addressed and GitHub Actions builds
  passed, the ultimate Vercel deployment failures were traced back to
  unconfigured environment variables on the Vercel platform, requiring direct
  user intervention."
